{"id":1992,"date":"2014-12-16T19:02:43","date_gmt":"2014-12-16T19:02:43","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/?p=1992"},"modified":"2015-12-17T17:17:51","modified_gmt":"2015-12-17T17:17:51","slug":"global-game-jam-2015-23rd-25th-january","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/2014\/12\/global-game-jam-2015-23rd-25th-january\/","title":{"rendered":"Global Game Jam 2015 | 23rd-25th January"},"content":{"rendered":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/global_game_jam_logo1.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-1993\" src=\"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/global_game_jam_logo1.jpg\" alt=\"#GGJ15\" width=\"488\" height=\"230\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http:\/\/globalgamejam.org\/\">Global Game Jam<\/a>\u00a0at Farset is back once more for 2015, in partnership with <a href=\"http:\/\/www.northernirelandscreen.co.uk\">Northern Ireland Screen<\/a>. \u00a0The Game Jam will run from <strong>Friday 23rd<\/strong> to <strong>Sunday 25th January<\/strong>, and is a chance to meet some great people and develop a fun game with a theme. The theme will be announced on the Friday night; there will be plenty of people there to team up with to create something interesting and, most importantly, to have fun!<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_2058\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-2058\" style=\"width: 640px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-2058 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com\/fsl-wordpress\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/12156638913_623893d6f9_z.jpg\" alt=\"12156638913_623893d6f9_z\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-2058\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Last Years Jam went very well, with all teams submitting something at the end of the weekend<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>How do I enter?<br \/>\n<\/strong><a href=\"http:\/\/globalgamejam.org\/user\/signup\/to\/participate\/using\">Register on the Global Game Jam site<\/a>\u00a0to participate, and\u00a0reserve your seat on\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.eventbrite.co.uk\/e\/global-game-jam-belfast-2015-tickets-14970200272\">our\u00a0Eventbrite listing<\/a> for the game jam. \u00a0The event is free, and meals are catered! \u00a0The theme will be announced at <strong>5pm on Friday 23rd January<\/strong>\u00a0(to accommodate Hawaii) so we recommend all participants to be in Farset before that time, or send word if you will be arriving later on. We look\u00a0forward to seeing you all for this, as it should be a great weekend!<\/p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>What do I need?<br \/>\n<\/strong>There is no required skill level or barrier for entry; we welcome programmers, artists, musicians and anyone else who might be interested in being involved! Bring yourself and your equipment\u00a0&#8211; the organisers recommend that participants wait until the beginning of the event to form teams. \u00a0We have found that this worked well in the past and gives interesting results.<\/p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">More information will be provided in the run-up, but please feel free to contact <a href=\"mailto:events@farsetlabs.org.uk\">events@farsetlabs.org.uk<\/a> or ask us questions via\u00a0<a title=\"Facebook\" href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/FarsetLabs?fref=ts\">Facebook<\/a> or <a title=\"Twitter\" href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/farsetlabs\">Twitter<\/a>\u00a0with the #GGJ15 tag.<\/p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Brought to\u00a0you to in partnership with Northern Ireland Screen, and with support from Iglu Media.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_2002\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-2002\" style=\"width: 309px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"http:\/\/www.northernirelandscreen.co.uk\/\" rel=\"http:\/\/www.northernirelandscreen.co.uk\/categories\/205\/digital-and-interactive.aspx\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-2002 \" src=\"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/NIScreen_logo1.jpg\" alt=\"NIScreen\" width=\"309\" height=\"110\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-2002\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Brought to you in partnership with NI Screen<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<figure id=\"attachment_2055\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-2055\" style=\"width: 128px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"http:\/\/www.iglumedia.co.uk\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-2055\" src=\"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/iglu-logo-black-sml.png\" alt=\"Iglu Media\" width=\"128\" height=\"130\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-2055\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Iglu Media<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>What is Global Game Jam?<br \/>\n<\/strong>Global Game Jam is essentially a\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Hackathon\">hackathon<\/a>, focused on games of all sorts, from full-scale console productions to mobile, web-based and embedded games, as well as non-digital productions like board and card games. Some will be frivolous, others developed for solid causes, such as social impact in the case of the\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/www.gamesforchange.org\/\">Games For Change<\/a>\u00a0movement. \u00a0There are already a number of large\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/globalgamejam.org\/sponsors\">sponsors<\/a>\u00a0involved in this year\u2019s global event, including Facebook, Unity and Github.<\/p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The first Global Game Jam ran\u00a0in 2009, and this year there are already over 480\u00a0individual Jam sites registered around the world. We will be live streaming video from sites all over during the 48hr event. There will also be an opportunity to see and\u00a0play other teams\u2019 games at the end of the event. The details of the venue\u00a0are also available\u00a0on our Global Game Jam\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/globalgamejam.org\/2015\/jam-sites\/farset-labs\">listing<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http:\/\/www.farsetlabs.org.uk\/assets\/docs\/15-jan-presspack.zip\" target=\"_blank\">Press Release<\/a><\/p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https:\/\/s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com\/fsl-wordpress\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/GlobalGameJam_belfast_poster.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2059\" src=\"https:\/\/s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com\/fsl-wordpress\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/12\/GlobalGameJam_belfast_poster.png\" alt=\"GlobalGameJam_belfast_poster\" width=\"769\" height=\"1088\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Global Game Jam\u00a0at Farset is back once more for 2015, in partnership with Northern Ireland Screen. \u00a0The Game Jam will run from Friday 23rd to Sunday 25th January, and is a chance to meet some great people and develop a fun game with a theme. The theme will be announced on the Friday night; there [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":8,"featured_media":2058,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[136],"tags":[891,160,715,689,99,974,973],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1992"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/8"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1992"}],"version-history":[{"count":9,"href":"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1992\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2188,"href":"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1992\/revisions\/2188"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/blog.farsetlabs.org.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/